d%20the%20most%20proven%20route%20to%20financial%20freedom%20that%20I%20abided%20by%20for%20the%20majority%20of%20my%20career%20as%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbest-online-financial-advisors%5C%22%3Ebest%20financial%20advisor%3C%2Fa%3E%20I%20could%20be.%20Every%20high%20net%20worth%20client%20I%20met%20with%20was%20confirmation%20of%20this%20strategy%2C%20as%20most%20of%20them%20were%20in%20their%20late%2050s%20and%2060s%20and%20had%20reached%20the%20million-dollar%20mark%20by%20delaying%20gratification%20and%20playing%20the%20long%20game.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20as%20tried%20and%20true%20as%20that%20method%20is%2C%20it%20doesn't%20mean%20that%20following%20it%20for%20decades%20is%20easy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20conversation%20that%20changed%20my%20thinking%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPersonal%20finance%20is%20essentially%20a%20series%20of%20trade-offs.%20Spend%20and%20enjoy%20the%20majority%20of%20your%20money%20now%20or%20delay%20those%20luxuries%20in%20exchange%20for%20a%20comfortable%20retirement%20in%20the%20future.%20Another%20common%20example%20is%20to%20sacrifice%20work-life%20balance%20and%20long%20hours%20in%20exchange%20for%20a%20higher%20salary.%20These%20trade-offs%20felt%20inevitable%20to%20me%2C%20so%20I%20opted%20for%20the%20modest%20yet%20consistent%20approach%20to%20wealth-building%20and%20delayed%20many%20of%20the%20lifestyle%20experiences%20I%20knew%20I%20wanted%20to%20enjoy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20changed%20when%20I%20interviewed%20then-30-year-old%20Grant%20Sabatier%20for%20a%20local%20New%20York%20City%20radio%20show%20in%202019.%20He'd%20amassed%20a%20net%20worth%20of%20%241.25%20million%20in%20just%20five%20years.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMidway%20through%20our%20interview%2C%20I%20asked%20Sabatier%20what%20the%20average%20person%20can%20do%20to%20achieve%20similar%20results.%20I%20wanted%20to%20know%20how%20to%20accelerate%20the%20wealth-building%20process%20while%20also%20enjoying%20the%20fruits%20of%20your%20hard%20work.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20the%20important%20thing%20is%20to%20really%20figure%20out%20what%20makes%20you%20happy%20in%20life%2C%26quot%3B%20Sabatier%20began.%20%26quot%3BThe%20most%20important%20question%20is%20not%20how%20much%20money%20do%20you%20need%2C%20but%20what%20kind%20of%20life%20do%20you%20want%20to%20live%3F%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20continued%20telling%20me%20that%20at%20age%2025%2C%20he%20sat%20down%20and%20listed%20the%2010%20things%20that%20made%20him%20happy.%20Eight%20of%20those%20items%2C%20which%20included%20spending%20time%20with%20family%2C%20were%20free%2C%20and%20the%20other%20two%20were%20%26quot%3Bpretty%20inexpensive.%26quot%3B%20The%20next%20step%20was%20to%20ask%2C%20%26quot%3BWhy%20can't%20I%20optimize%20my%20life%20to%20have%20more%20time%20to%20do%20those%20things%3F%20I%20realized%20that%20I%20needed%20a%20lot%20less%20money%20than%20I%20thought%20to%20be%20happy%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Sabatier.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20that%20point%20in%20the%20interview%2C%20things%20clicked%20for%20me.%20I%20began%20to%20reorganize%20my%20own%20finances%20to%20better%20fit%20the%20life%20I%20truly%20wanted%20to%20live.%20Since%20that%202019%20conversation%2C%20I've%20become%20a%20homeowner%20and%20increased%20my%20income%20by%20%2450%2C000%20while%20also%20staying%20on%20track%20to%20pay%20off%20my%20undergraduate%20loans%20this%20year%20and%20travel%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20are%20the%20steps%20I%20took%20to%20create%20and%20maintain%20balance%20in%20my%20financial%20life.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20made%20a%20list%20of%20the%20things%20that%20make%20me%20happy%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20by%20listing%20a%20few%20things%20that%20make%20me%20happy%3B%20at%20this%20step%2C%20I%20didn't%20limit%20the%20list%20based%20on%20how%20much%20something%20costs%20or%20the%20time%20restraints.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20me%2C%20watching%20college%20football%20in%20the%20fall%20is%20something%20that%20made%20me%20happy%2C%20so%20attending%20more%20live%20games%20was%20something%20that%20I%20wanted%20my%20lifestyle%20to%20include.%20Growing%20up%20in%20Oklahoma%2C%20college%20football%20was%20our%20rite%20of%20passage%2C%20and%20watching%20games%20reminds%20me%20of%20the%20Saturday%20mornings%20when%20we%20would%20gather%20around%20the%20TV%20to%20watch%20%26quot%3BCollege%20GameDay%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20tradition%20I%20continue%20with%20my%20kids%20today.%20But%20I%20had%20never%20attended%20a%20game%20in%20person%2C%20so%20I%20made%20a%20point%20to%20change%20that.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20item%20on%20my%20list%20was%20learning%20to%20play%20an%20instrument%3B%20due%20to%20the%20demands%20of%20my%20career%2C%20I%20often%20felt%20like%20I%20didn't%20have%20the%20time.%20I%20added%20it%20to%20my%20list.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20broke%20the%20list%20into%20smaller%20items%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20make%20my%20goal%20feasible%2C%20I%20decided%20to%20go%20to%20just%20one%20major%20football%20game%20each%20year.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDepending%20on%20your%20goals%2C%20it%20may%20not%20be%20feasible%20or%20realistic%20to%20tackle%20them%20all%20at%20once%3B%20that's%20OK.%20This%20is%20where%20you'll%20want%20to%20break%20your%20goals%20down%20into%20sprints%2C%20small%20goals%2C%20and%20milestones%20that%20won't%20take%20you%20away%20from%20reaching%20your%20long-term%20financial%20goals.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20priced%20out%20my%20list%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3ENext%2C%20I%20gathered%20estimates%20for%20what%20each%20item%20would%20cost.%20When%20I%20was%20ready%20to%20learn%20an%20instrument%2C%20for%20example%2C%20I%20started%20by%20purchasing%20a%20used%20trumpet%20for%20%24300%20in%202021%2C%20and%20as%20I%20improved%2C%20I%20bought%20a%20brand%20new%20one.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20one%20or%20m